WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.120
Once someone comes out,
follow their directions.

00:00:05.850 --> 00:00:07.220
It's been fun.

00:00:07.220 --> 00:00:08.200
Good luck.

00:00:08.200 --> 00:00:09.740
Yeah, thank you.

00:00:14.740 --> 00:00:17.270
Is this Mikhail's residence?

00:00:17.980 --> 00:00:21.000
Go do some shopping at
Dick Sakura, by the station.

00:00:21.220 --> 00:00:23.750
At check out, give the cashier this card.

00:00:26.530 --> 00:00:28.500
Please come this way, sir.

00:01:57.970 --> 00:02:03.020
Strategy x And x Scheme

00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:10.320
There are more people this time.

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:16.870
I wonder if there's anyone I know.

00:02:19.020 --> 00:02:19.910
Yo.

00:02:20.190 --> 00:02:22.550
Last year, you had your way with us.

00:02:22.550 --> 00:02:24.980
But that won't happen again.

00:02:24.980 --> 00:02:28.170
We've undergone some hellish training.

00:02:28.730 --> 00:02:32.040
Our teamwork is perfect now.

00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:36.800
Thank you for coming!

00:02:38.170 --> 00:02:42.800
This year, 1,489 applicants
have made it this far,

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:48.060
but the Phase Two examiner has asked me
to trim that number to about 300.

00:02:48.770 --> 00:02:50.760
As for the exam...

00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:52.840
There are two hours before lunch.

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.690
Defeat five people before then.

00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:56.950
Grab their tags when you defeat them,

00:02:56.950 --> 00:02:59.200
and see me when you have all five.

00:02:59.510 --> 00:03:01.320
I'll wait on the other side of the door.

00:03:01.750 --> 00:03:02.500
Got it?

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:04.580
As soon as I shut the door,

00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:06.580
you may start.

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:13.840
Every stage of the exam should be like this...

00:03:14.770 --> 00:03:18.630
You've gotta be strong to be a Hunter.

00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:27.670
Oh, you're here!

00:03:27.670 --> 00:03:28.620
Killu—

00:03:30.680 --> 00:03:31.860
Sucks for you.

00:03:32.290 --> 00:03:34.440
I'm the only one passing this year.

00:03:35.490 --> 00:03:37.820
He's totally out of our league...

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:42.120
So that's what it takes to
become a top Hunter...

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:46.640
This will be the last time I
attempt the Hunter Exam...

00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:56.950
We finally have our first applicant.

00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:00.160
That took an hour and a half.

00:04:00.600 --> 00:04:01.680
What happened to everyone else?

00:04:02.310 --> 00:04:03.330
They're all asleep.

00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:08.910
It took me a while to collect all their tags.

00:04:13.430 --> 00:04:15.300
Is there going to be a second stage?

00:04:17.910 --> 00:04:20.390
That won't be necessary.

00:04:20.390 --> 00:04:23.680
He's demonstrated his skill.

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:27.320
Killua, denizen of the darkness...

00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:31.000
He's returned much stronger.

00:04:31.780 --> 00:04:35.030
Applicant 1219, Killua-kun.

00:04:35.030 --> 00:04:35.960
Yeah.

00:04:36.410 --> 00:04:37.460
You've passed

00:04:39.450 --> 00:04:40.480
the Hunter Exam!

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:48.190
Welcome back, Killua.

00:04:48.190 --> 00:04:49.370
How was the exam?

00:04:49.370 --> 00:04:51.520
I passed it in no time, naturally.

00:04:52.170 --> 00:04:53.440
Yay!

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:58.030
Sorry to interrupt your celebration,
but look at these spell cards.

00:04:59.690 --> 00:05:01.040
Wow...

00:05:01.040 --> 00:05:02.990
There's even an S-rank card!

00:05:02.990 --> 00:05:05.110
How much can we sell it for?

00:05:05.110 --> 00:05:08.010
Oh, let's go ask around!

00:05:08.010 --> 00:05:10.540
No, we should use it wisely.

00:05:11.050 --> 00:05:12.740
So what should we do?

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:15.110
Well, I guess it's safe to hold on to it.

00:05:15.530 --> 00:05:17.190
With all these defensive spells,

00:05:17.190 --> 00:05:19.300
we don't need to worry
about it getting stolen.

00:05:19.960 --> 00:05:21.690
Have you tried any of these?

00:05:21.690 --> 00:05:23.650
Just Blackout Curtain.

00:05:23.650 --> 00:05:24.780
What?

00:05:24.780 --> 00:05:26.930
If you have all these cards,
you should use them...

00:05:27.290 --> 00:05:29.730
Start by using this one.

00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:34.020
You can choose a player you've
met before, and talk to them.

00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:34.020
Contact
Communicate with one target
player (encountered within the
game) via your Book.
(Connection maintained for
a maximum of 3 minutes.
May only be broken by
player who used this card.)
[LR][NORM]

00:05:34.450 --> 00:05:36.090
Who should we talk to?

00:05:36.090 --> 00:05:38.030
We won't know until we see who's available.

00:05:38.640 --> 00:05:40.030
Contact on!

00:05:45.440 --> 00:05:47.660
Oh, I see a lot of names.

00:05:50.840 --> 00:05:51.840
Hey, Gon...

00:05:51.840 --> 00:05:53.560
When did you run into him?

00:05:53.560 --> 00:05:54.450
Huh?

00:05:58.250 --> 00:06:01.010
Chrollo Lucilfer

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:00.570
Chrollo?

00:06:01.340 --> 00:06:03.120
Who's Chrollo?

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:06.210
I haven't seen Chrollo inside the game.

00:06:06.210 --> 00:06:09.050
Does that mean you guys passed
each other without noticing?

00:06:09.050 --> 00:06:10.640
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:06:10.900 --> 00:06:12.260
That doesn't make sense.

00:06:12.260 --> 00:06:15.020
Kurapika sealed his <i>Nen</i>.

00:06:15.270 --> 00:06:18.900
Yeah, and you have to use
<i>Nen</i> to enter the game.

00:06:18.900 --> 00:06:20.620
Who's Kurapika?!

00:06:20.620 --> 00:06:22.320
That only leaves...

00:06:23.600 --> 00:06:25.630
Let me in on this!

00:06:29.110 --> 00:06:31.330
I get it. So that's what's going on.

00:06:32.910 --> 00:06:34.250
Hey, Shal...

00:06:34.250 --> 00:06:36.430
Stop laughing, and explain
what this is about.

00:06:36.430 --> 00:06:37.830
Sorry about that.

00:06:37.830 --> 00:06:40.710
Chrollo Lucilfer

00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:40.710
This probably isn't the boss.

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:43.840
He hasn't purged the <i>Nen</i> from his body.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.200
Purging <i>Nen</i>?

00:06:46.200 --> 00:06:47.090
It's very doable.

00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:48.050
Seriously?

00:06:48.050 --> 00:06:49.170
Of course!

00:06:49.170 --> 00:06:50.960
If you can place <i>Nen</i> on others,

00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:53.350
it's not unreasonable to think
<i>Nen</i> can be removed, as well.

00:06:53.800 --> 00:06:58.100
Does that mean Chrollo has removed
Kurapika's <i>Nen</i>, and entered the game?

00:06:58.360 --> 00:06:59.860
Why would he be here?

00:06:59.860 --> 00:07:01.500
I'm not sure,

00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:03.670
but we should probably let Kurapika know.

00:07:04.310 --> 00:07:06.600
I'll leave the game real quick.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:08.740
You can use a spell card to leave.

00:07:09.570 --> 00:07:10.800
Save it.

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:12.440
I can be out and back in four hours.

00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:16.240
I should have realized this sooner...

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:21.000
Yorknew City                                        Greed Island

00:07:17.210 --> 00:07:21.000
This island is directly east of Yorknew City.

00:07:23.410 --> 00:07:25.340
East is the direction to go.

00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:28.190
You will find one who awaits you.

00:07:28.750 --> 00:07:29.800
I see.

00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:32.600
So the boss came here to find
someone to purge that <i>Nen</i>.

00:07:33.450 --> 00:07:36.760
The boss arrived the same way we did,

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:38.260
but then Razor kicked him out.

00:07:38.260 --> 00:07:40.790
That was when he realized
this was Greed Island.

00:07:41.300 --> 00:07:43.840
But since the boss can't use <i>Nen</i>,

00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:46.400
he can't enter the island
via the usual channels.

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:50.160
So he must have hired someone
to come to this island for him.

00:07:50.750 --> 00:07:54.750
He had them use his name
as a hidden message to us.

00:07:56.660 --> 00:08:00.010
The one who can purge this
<i>Nen</i> is on Greed Island.

00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:04.550
Change in plans again...

00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:06.860
Let's bring everyone else here.

00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:10.290
Yes, we'll all start looking
for this <i>Nen</i> exorcist.

00:08:10.290 --> 00:08:12.170
I have a small correction.

00:08:15.760 --> 00:08:16.990
You're...

00:08:16.990 --> 00:08:17.900
Hisoka!

00:08:18.820 --> 00:08:22.640
It was my idea to use Chrollo's name.

00:08:23.290 --> 00:08:26.690
Because I didn't know you could
enter any name you like

00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:29.710
until I was already inside...

00:08:30.970 --> 00:08:32.390
You should praise my initiative.

00:08:32.790 --> 00:08:36.580
Since I helped you understand Chrollo's message.

00:08:36.940 --> 00:08:39.010
Ah, so that's what this is about.

00:08:39.490 --> 00:08:42.330
I'm dying to kill you right here and now,

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:44.260
but I'll let the boss do that.

00:08:46.060 --> 00:08:49.550
Well, if anything comes up,
use Contact to get in touch.

00:08:50.070 --> 00:08:53.020
If I learn anything new, I'll let you know.

00:08:54.360 --> 00:08:55.280
Bye.

00:08:58.680 --> 00:09:01.230
So the boss hired Hisoka...

00:09:01.640 --> 00:09:03.820
He probably didn't have much
choice, but it's still weird.

00:09:03.820 --> 00:09:07.060
And his reward is probably a duel,
once the boss is cleansed.

00:09:07.550 --> 00:09:10.150
But now, it's only a matter of time

00:09:12.060 --> 00:09:13.810
until the boss comes back!

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:17.910
I doubt it.

00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:19.700
I would know at once

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:24.660
if <i>Nen</i> I placed on a spider
had been removed.

00:09:25.250 --> 00:09:29.370
So when you chose your power, you
knew something like this might happen?

00:09:29.700 --> 00:09:30.810
Of course...

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:33.230
If you're able to place <i>Nen</i> on others,

00:09:33.230 --> 00:09:36.350
it only makes sense to assume

00:09:36.350 --> 00:09:38.810
that one can also remove <i>Nen</i>.

00:09:40.020 --> 00:09:42.500
Well, now you know.

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:44.060
What you do from here is up to you.

00:09:44.450 --> 00:09:46.010
Thanks for taking the trouble.

00:09:46.330 --> 00:09:47.340
You have my gratitude.

00:09:51.690 --> 00:09:52.740
Did you need anything?

00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:57.690
What am I...

00:09:58.360 --> 00:10:00.430
What am I supposed to do this month?

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:02.570
Tell me...

00:10:03.150 --> 00:10:04.950
What should I do?

00:10:05.680 --> 00:10:08.150
It'll be fine. Let me handle...

00:10:08.150 --> 00:10:09.710
What could you possibly know?

00:10:10.270 --> 00:10:13.990
You have no idea what's going
to happen to us now!

00:10:14.610 --> 00:10:15.990
Neon... I need Neon!

00:10:15.990 --> 00:10:17.800
Restore Neon at once!

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:24.020
Damn! Why did this happen?

00:10:27.290 --> 00:10:28.870
I wonder what's wrong...

00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:33.000
Why did it stop working?

00:10:35.070 --> 00:10:35.990
See ya.

00:10:39.410 --> 00:10:42.430
Looks like it's not the real Chrollo.

00:10:42.430 --> 00:10:43.500
Oh...

00:10:43.750 --> 00:10:46.380
Kurapika was pretty calm about it.

00:10:46.750 --> 00:10:49.460
Like he wasn't concerned or just didn't care.

00:10:50.130 --> 00:10:53.010
Well, it sounds like you
got worried for nothing.

00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:56.260
Now it's time to focus on yourselves.

00:10:56.540 --> 00:10:57.300
Osu!

00:10:57.300 --> 00:10:58.800
Start with the basics...

00:10:59.240 --> 00:11:00.760
We're not going to train.

00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:02.650
It's time to start

00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:05.530
beating this game!

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:14.150
It's said the legendary King Great White Beetle

00:11:14.150 --> 00:11:16.080
lives only on this tree!

00:11:16.590 --> 00:11:19.120
There's only one way to capture it!

00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:21.450
Hit the tree hard enough to shake it out.

00:11:22.470 --> 00:11:24.370
First comes rock!

00:11:24.990 --> 00:11:26.160
Rock, paper...

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:27.770
Rock!

00:11:32.390 --> 00:11:33.840
Wow!

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:35.630
It's raining bugs!

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:37.270
Found it.

00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:39.370
Difficulty rank A!

00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:41.140
King Great White Beetle
A legendary insect that
releases pheromones
which attract other insects
to start a massive colony.
Can only leave the colony
for brief evening walks.

00:11:39.370 --> 00:11:43.040
That's three King Great White Beetle cards!

00:11:43.670 --> 00:11:46.270
You could've gotten more if
you'd thrown a real punch.

00:11:46.780 --> 00:11:49.990
Well, I didn't want to damage the tree.

00:11:52.070 --> 00:11:54.280
There is no such girl in this mansion.

00:11:55.010 --> 00:11:57.930
Even if there were, it would be impossible

00:11:57.930 --> 00:12:00.830
for you to bypass all the traps and find her.

00:12:00.830 --> 00:12:02.280
Found her.

00:12:03.050 --> 00:12:05.140
She was in a hidden room,
four floors underground.

00:12:05.140 --> 00:12:05.910
What?

00:12:05.910 --> 00:12:07.540
Curse you!

00:12:09.230 --> 00:12:12.170
Got an A-rank Gold Dust Girl!

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:10.790
Gold Dust Girl
A girl who releases golden dust.
One bath a day will net approx. 500 G.
Very shy and quiet.

00:12:12.170 --> 00:12:14.050
The guard was a rank F.

00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:17.640
Next, let's head to the
City of Gambling, Dorias!

00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:20.440
Wait, wasn't today supposed to be

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:22.360
the monthly contest in Antokiba?

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:24.560
We'll be passing through, so let's give it a go.

00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:29.560
Our winner is the Killua and Gon team.

00:12:29.870 --> 00:12:32.560
A Paladin's Necklace! Score!

00:12:29.870 --> 00:12:32.560
Paladin's Necklace
When a player wears this,
all spells targeting player
will be reflected.
Can also dispel curses
placed on any card
touched by player.

00:12:33.070 --> 00:12:35.850
I don't understand this description.

00:12:35.850 --> 00:12:37.820
We can ask one of the shopkeepers.

00:12:38.300 --> 00:12:41.430
When you wear this necklace,

00:12:41.430 --> 00:12:43.950
you can reflect all attack spells.

00:12:44.520 --> 00:12:47.550
And if you touch cards under the

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:46.930 position:80% line:20%
Transform
Change one card in your possession into any
other card in your possession. (Card will now
count against the limit of new card type. If limit has already been reached, nothing will happen,
and the Transform card will be destroyed.)
[SR][NORM]

00:12:46.930 --> 00:12:49.960 position:80% line:20%
Fake
Change Fake into any card type from 001 to 099.
The new card can be placed in a restricted pocket.
But it will not count toward Book completion,
and cannot be transformed into an item.
It also will not count toward card limit.
[SR][NORM]

00:12:47.550 --> 00:12:49.960
effects of Transform or Fake,

00:12:49.960 --> 00:12:52.340
you can restore them to their original state.

00:12:52.740 --> 00:12:53.990
Wow...

00:12:53.990 --> 00:12:57.300
If we wear this, we won't have to
worry about losing any cards.

00:12:59.250 --> 00:13:00.990
Memory Helmet...

00:12:59.450 --> 00:13:01.070
Memory Helmet
A player will always remember
everything seen or heard
while wearing this item.
Unfortunately, helmet is
very large and heavy.

00:13:00.990 --> 00:13:02.370
Witch's Love Potion.

00:13:01.070 --> 00:13:02.570
Witch's Love Potion
If player kisses a pill before
feeding it to a target, target will
become beholden to player.
Each pill will remain effective
for one week. Each bottle
contains 500 pills.

00:13:02.370 --> 00:13:04.010
Risky Dice.

00:13:02.570 --> 00:13:04.200
Risky Dice
A 20-sided die. One side says
Bad Luck, while the other nineteen
say Good Luck. If player rolls
Good Luck, something good will
happen. But if player rolls Bad Luck,
something bad will happen to cancel
out everything that was good.

00:13:04.010 --> 00:13:06.130
King Great White Beetle.

00:13:04.200 --> 00:13:06.240
King Great White Beetle
A legendary insect that
releases pheromones
which attract other insects
to start a massive colony.
Can only leave the colony
for brief evening walks.

00:13:06.130 --> 00:13:07.660
Gold Dust Girl.

00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:07.330
Gold Dust Girl
A girl who releases golden dust.
One bath a day will net approx. 500 G.
Very shy and quiet.

00:13:07.330 --> 00:13:09.230
Paladin's Necklace
When a player wears this,
all spells targeting player
will be reflected.
Can also dispel curses
placed on any card
