00:13:07.660 --> 00:13:09.230
Paladin's Necklace.

00:13:09.710 --> 00:13:12.400
A total of six different restricted slot cards!

00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:13.890
Piece of cake!

00:13:14.480 --> 00:13:15.720
Piece of cake?

00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:16.980
Not in the least.

00:13:17.320 --> 00:13:20.520
This was only possible because you
underwent that grueling training.

00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:26.990
Another player has used Contact to reach you.

00:13:28.040 --> 00:13:30.040
Yo. It's been a while, Gon.

00:13:30.800 --> 00:13:31.720
Who are you?

00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:34.320
You don't remember me?

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:36.000
Do you remember the player

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:39.990
who took the Sword of Truth
from you in Antokiba?

00:13:41.060 --> 00:13:42.010
What do you want?

00:13:42.380 --> 00:13:43.500
Up for a trade?

00:13:43.840 --> 00:13:49.810
I have #66, Witch's Diet Pill,
and #17, VIP Multi-Pass.

00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.430
You can talk it over with your friends.

00:13:53.110 --> 00:13:54.070
What do you think?

00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:04.700
Another player has used Contact to reach you.

00:14:05.100 --> 00:14:06.470
It's Tsezgerra.

00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:07.630
You again?

00:14:08.060 --> 00:14:09.780
Interested in trading your

00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:12.730
Breath of Archangel for our Patch of Forest?

00:14:12.730 --> 00:14:14.210
It's an SS-rank card.

00:14:14.410 --> 00:14:15.680
No way.

00:14:15.680 --> 00:14:18.870
I've already said I won't
deal with you people.

00:14:18.870 --> 00:14:21.020
What if I throw in a Clone?

00:14:21.020 --> 00:14:23.720
I'm telling you that there's no deal here.

00:14:24.060 --> 00:14:27.030
You already have ninety-two different cards.

00:14:27.660 --> 00:14:28.930
All that's left

00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:31.890
are the cards monopolized
by other players, yes?

00:14:32.870 --> 00:14:36.140
Actually, we have ninety-five...

00:14:36.140 --> 00:14:40.110
And you probably have many items
that you haven't used Gain on yet.

00:14:40.480 --> 00:14:46.490
It's possible that Breath of Archangel
is the final card you need.

00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:52.440
If we give that to you, we'll lose.

00:14:54.140 --> 00:14:55.870
Stop playing dumb.

00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:59.010
I know that you're monopolizing

00:14:59.010 --> 00:15:03.130
both Breath of Archangel and Night Jade.

00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:05.290
This game isn't over yet.

00:15:05.290 --> 00:15:06.130
I see.

00:15:06.520 --> 00:15:08.480
Good luck, then.

00:15:08.930 --> 00:15:11.420
But we'll never let you have these cards.

00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:13.390
What if I offer three cards?

00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:17.110
We'll give you Patch of Forest,

00:15:14.960 --> 00:15:16.670
Patch of Forest
The entrance to an enormous
forest known as the Mountain
God's Garden. Many species
exist only in this forest.
All are friendly to humans.

00:15:16.670 --> 00:15:18.420
Hidden Hollow
Upon entering and exiting hollow,
player will be transported to a
desolate location. However, player can
return to original location
without spending any money.

00:15:17.110 --> 00:15:18.870
Hidden Hollow,

00:15:18.420 --> 00:15:20.270
Palmtop Dragon
As the name implies, this dragon
fits on your palm. Willingly obeys
its master. If raised lovingly,
it can learn to speak.

00:15:18.870 --> 00:15:20.270
and Palmtop Dragon.

00:15:21.340 --> 00:15:25.280
And you only have to give us Night Jade,
not Breath of Archangel.

00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:29.430
We'd be giving you one SS-rank
card and two S-rank cards,

00:15:29.430 --> 00:15:31.750
while you'd only give up one A-rank card.

00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:33.790
I believe this deal is too good to pass up.

00:15:36.010 --> 00:15:37.890
Give us some time to discuss this.

00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:40.370
Just to be clear, this is our final offer.

00:15:40.880 --> 00:15:43.110
We won't accept any further negotiation.

00:15:43.800 --> 00:15:44.500
Book.

00:15:45.990 --> 00:15:47.510
It's gotta be a trap.

00:15:47.510 --> 00:15:49.190
That offer's too good.

00:15:49.190 --> 00:15:51.620
Tsezgerra is a careful man.

00:15:51.620 --> 00:15:53.680
He wouldn't try to pick a fight.

00:15:54.030 --> 00:15:57.610
But at the same time, he would
never make a losing deal.

00:15:57.870 --> 00:16:02.190
Breath of Archangel
An angel who can cure any mortal
injury or terminal disease with one breath.
However, angel will appear only once.

00:15:58.020 --> 00:15:59.930
Meaning that he thinks

00:15:59.930 --> 00:16:02.190
he can obtain a Breath of Archangel.

00:16:02.580 --> 00:16:07.110
Does that mean they've assembled
all forty spell card types?

00:16:07.360 --> 00:16:08.500
It's possible.

00:16:08.810 --> 00:16:12.200
So they're waiting for Gain to be
used on a Breath of Archangel.

00:16:12.200 --> 00:16:18.710
Night Jade
A jewel blessed by the devil.
When the holder is in danger,
peril will be shifted to another.

00:16:12.710 --> 00:16:15.050
On the other hand, Night Jade is a card

00:16:15.050 --> 00:16:16.660
that we monopolized through hard work.

00:16:17.300 --> 00:16:19.500
If one of the cards were to be destroyed,

00:16:19.500 --> 00:16:22.960
one of our jade jewels would
automatically turn into a card.

00:16:23.850 --> 00:16:28.080
Which means the A-rank
Night Jade is much harder

00:16:28.080 --> 00:16:31.220
for them to get than the
SS-rank Breath of Archangel.

00:16:32.560 --> 00:16:34.150
This is a gamble.

00:16:35.370 --> 00:16:38.730
Witch's Love Potion
If player kisses a pill before
feeding it to a target, target will
become beholden to player.
Each pill will remain effective
for one week. Each bottle
contains 500 pills.

00:16:36.200 --> 00:16:38.730
VIP Multi-Pass
Present this pass to gain
entry into any location.
Contains 1000 passes.

00:16:41.810 --> 00:16:42.590
Book.

00:16:43.860 --> 00:16:44.620
See ya.

00:16:52.260 --> 00:16:54.430
That was uneventful.

00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:56.180
Kind of disappointing.

00:16:56.560 --> 00:16:58.100
I was so nervous...

00:16:58.760 --> 00:17:01.250
But now we've gathered
seven types, in three days!

00:17:01.740 --> 00:17:03.450
We're making decent progress.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:05.930
Okay, let's keep this up.

00:17:06.340 --> 00:17:09.920
Are there any other events in the city
for getting restricted slot cards?

00:17:09.920 --> 00:17:13.260
Hmm... I think there are...

00:17:14.340 --> 00:17:16.090
Prizes from the slot machines?

00:17:16.570 --> 00:17:19.020
Should've expected as much from
Dorias, the City of Gambling.

00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:22.200
You have a 0.01% chance of winning.

00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:24.000
That's one in ten thousand tries.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:25.540
So it all comes down to luck.

00:17:25.900 --> 00:17:27.230
Pretty risky.

00:17:28.720 --> 00:17:29.740
I know, Gon!

00:17:29.740 --> 00:17:30.660
Use that dice!

00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:32.260
This is it...

00:17:32.260 --> 00:17:34.160
If we get Good Luck, we can win!

00:17:34.430 --> 00:17:36.420
But if you get Bad Luck,

00:17:36.420 --> 00:17:38.740
something bad will happen that cancels out

00:17:38.740 --> 00:17:40.300
everything good that's happened.

00:17:40.300 --> 00:17:43.170
There's only a one in twenty
chance of getting Bad Luck.

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:46.470
There!

00:17:47.510 --> 00:17:49.550
Next, we try the slot machine!

00:17:53.190 --> 00:17:55.010
Awesome! One try!

00:17:55.370 --> 00:17:57.390
Rainbow Diamond
A diamond that glitters like
a rainbow. If this diamond
is presented when proposing,
you will never be turned down.

00:17:55.500 --> 00:17:57.390
A Rainbow Diamond! Score!

00:17:57.880 --> 00:17:59.260
That's what I thought...

00:17:59.260 --> 00:18:02.640
This die is the key to winning in this city.

00:18:02.880 --> 00:18:06.950
But if you roll Bad Luck, it could be scary.

00:18:06.950 --> 00:18:08.520
Don't worry.

00:18:08.520 --> 00:18:10.180
It can't kill me...

00:18:11.240 --> 00:18:14.160
Oh, no! A slot machine exploded!

00:18:14.420 --> 00:18:16.220
I knew something was wrong.

00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:18.910
That guy hit the jackpot five times in a row.

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:21.400
And he was acting weird...

00:18:21.400 --> 00:18:23.310
He kept rolling a funny-looking die.

00:18:23.910 --> 00:18:27.290
Yikes, his face is mush...

00:18:28.670 --> 00:18:31.300
Anyway, let's make the trade.

00:18:31.550 --> 00:18:36.090
Yeah, we want to get cards of rank S
and above as quickly as possible.

00:18:36.460 --> 00:18:37.890
Yeah.

00:18:37.890 --> 00:18:40.060
As for cards rank A and below...

00:18:43.210 --> 00:18:44.080
Roll.

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:46.310
S-Spare me...

00:18:46.680 --> 00:18:49.040
This is only your third time.

00:18:49.040 --> 00:18:50.190
You'll be fine.

00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:55.220
I-I know someone who got
Bad Luck on the first roll and died!

00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:57.930
If I roll Bad Luck,

00:18:57.930 --> 00:19:01.860
I'll be hit for every Good Luck
that the other players rolled!

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:03.120
Not my problem.

00:19:03.530 --> 00:19:04.330
Roll.

00:19:04.330 --> 00:19:07.150
Or would you rather die right now?

00:19:15.650 --> 00:19:16.680
Come on...

00:19:21.960 --> 00:19:22.840
See?

00:19:22.840 --> 00:19:25.270
It's pretty rare to get Bad Luck.

00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:28.020
Now we use the Lottery card.

00:19:29.370 --> 00:19:33.690
We want #75, Lucky Alexandrite.

00:19:34.290 --> 00:19:37.280
If you obtain one, we'll set you free.

00:19:37.480 --> 00:19:39.240
C-Come on...

00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:40.630
Lottery on!

00:19:43.230 --> 00:19:43.940
Well?

00:19:44.900 --> 00:19:46.430
#76!

00:19:46.430 --> 00:19:48.270
So close!

00:19:48.610 --> 00:19:50.270
Your luck sucks.

00:19:50.270 --> 00:19:52.020
Okay, one more time!

00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:53.770
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

00:19:53.770 --> 00:19:57.980
Time for Motarike-kun to
show us what he's got!

00:20:01.060 --> 00:20:02.440
No good, huh?

00:20:03.730 --> 00:20:04.700
Hey, Gen.

00:20:04.990 --> 00:20:06.930
Should we make the first move?

00:20:07.350 --> 00:20:10.520
I already told you that combat
should be our last resort.

00:20:10.520 --> 00:20:11.440
It's too early for that.

00:20:11.900 --> 00:20:14.940
No, we're trying to stay
one step ahead of them.

00:20:15.430 --> 00:20:17.530
Though, once we commit,

00:20:17.530 --> 00:20:20.190
further negotiation will be impossible.

00:20:20.670 --> 00:20:22.200
What do you have in mind?

00:20:22.240 --> 00:20:26.950
Tax Collector's Gauntlet
When equipped, player has
the ability to cast Levy. But
each cast will destroy a random
card from player's restricted
slots. (Cannot use Levy if
restricted slots are empty.)

00:20:22.760 --> 00:20:24.820
We use Tax Collector's Gauntlet,

00:20:24.820 --> 00:20:26.950
combined with Risky Dice.

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:30.380
I understand.

00:20:30.380 --> 00:20:33.990
We use this to steal eight cards
from them immediately...

00:20:34.440 --> 00:20:36.460
But it's definitely dangerous.

00:20:36.870 --> 00:20:39.870
If someone rolls Bad Luck, they'll probably die.

00:20:40.450 --> 00:20:44.030
But this job is too important to leave to them.

00:20:44.690 --> 00:20:45.470
We can do this!

00:20:45.860 --> 00:20:48.430
We've come this far.
Let's clear the game.

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:52.730
Hey, Gen...

00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:54.460
What are you up to?

00:20:54.460 --> 00:20:56.260
I've told you this many times.

00:20:56.560 --> 00:21:00.630
When taking a risk, we three share the danger.

00:21:12.840 --> 00:21:14.030
It's Tsezgerra.

00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:15.370
Have you reached a decision?

00:21:15.370 --> 00:21:17.860
Okay, you have a deal.

00:21:23.030 --> 00:21:23.890
I can do this...

00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:26.470
One more time!

00:21:26.470 --> 00:21:28.270
I said I can do this,

00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:30.690
so I'm gonna do it!

00:21:33.410 --> 00:21:37.350
Okay, let's move on to the next city!

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:43.440
Gon's team has begun
working to beat the game.

00:21:43.440 --> 00:21:46.470
The story is nearing its climax.

00:22:57.150 --> 00:23:04.260
G.I. Tutorial

00:22:57.840 --> 00:23:00.900
Coming up, it's the
Greed Island Tutorial!

00:23:03.200 --> 00:23:05.390
Today, we introduce the card Lottery.

00:23:04.240 --> 00:23:14.870
Lottery
Change this card
into a random item card.
[SR][NORM]

00:23:05.390 --> 00:23:09.370
When you use this card,
it changes into a random card.

00:23:09.370 --> 00:23:12.360
That's why it's effective to use with Risky Dice.

00:23:15.420 --> 00:23:17.250
Continue!

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:23.880
Next time: 15 X 15.

00:23:24.270 --> 00:23:26.130
Hey, Killua, is this fifteen?

00:23:26.130 --> 00:23:27.470
What did you think it was?

00:23:27.470 --> 00:23:28.810
One five.

00:23:28.810 --> 00:23:30.400
Cute, huh...
